Winner of the seventh edition of the Nigerian Idol will go home with N100m grand prize. The battle is between Zadok and Progress. The finale will take place on Sunday May 22, 2022 with the show’s host, IK Osakioduwa, announcing the winner. After weeks of watching the top 12 contestants sing their hearts out on the live shows to earn fan votes, the competition is down to two finalists –Progress and Zadok – vying for the title of ‘Nigerian Idol’.   Davido’s first daughter resumes chores weekend, says…     Community leader tasks BBNaija organisers on modest…     Tiwa Savage gets special award in London   The winner will go home with a cash prize of N30 million, a brand new SUV, a Bigi branded refrigerator and a year’s supply of Bigi drinks. The winner and runner-up will also get to record an EP and a music video, a weekend getaway from TravelBeta, and a DStv Explora fully installed with a 12 months premium subscription. As a platform created to help exceptional musicians, the first runner-up will also walk away with an EP produced by a leading music producer in Nigeria and a top-notch music video shoot. Attachments area